What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Absolutely take this course with Professor Singh. The time you put into preparing for discussion is always worth it. One of the best seminars that I have ever taken at Yale.
I would definitely recommmend this course to other students. Seminars are interesting and the readings are not only interesting, but also definitely very worthwhile material for discussion.

Professor did a great job of encouraging discussion, but I wish he shared more of his own analyses. As a result, a lot of the analysis done in class was not very deep. Learned a lot, but did not learn as much as I hoped about the relationship between religion and politics.
